caption: Great food and service,  a real hipster environment
username: Inesina pan y Vina Y sus libros

caption: Stunning interiors and food was so well presented. For drinks, we ordered cappuccino, mochaccino (not on the menu, but s/o to our server Angela who made it to perfection!) and oat latte; Food - mushroom and parmesan egg benny, fried egg sammie (best brioche I have had, so very soft!), poached pear (very distinct flavors) and black velvet pancakes for food. Everything was delish! Decent portion size. Prices are almost similar to other brunch places in town. Its a hidden gem, recommend trying out once.  Taking out one star because service was bit slow, it felt that they were understaffed. Went on a Sunday afternoon and it was packed. They don't take reservations but checking on Yelp for waiting time helps!

We ordered takeout so I had anticipated the breakfast wouldn't be as fresh as hoped for but even then I was pretty disappointed. Sure it's to be expected that the yolk would break on our sandwiches.. but we were not given any napkins nor were we given cutlery for our hash browns ... I even ordered the Korean potato's as my side but only received regular hash browns. The cherry on top of this underwhelming experience was the hair I found under the lid of my takeout iced mocha. Quite disappointed in our experience and hopefully in the future brekkie cares for their takeout customers as much as their dine in customers.

The staff here were so friendly and the food was incredible. The store was clean and the atmosphere was amazing, I love that you get your own plants on your table. The service was fast and the waiter was knowledgeable. The presentation of the food was exquisite and cooked to perfection.  They are also doing an amazing job with guidelines for covid 19. Everything was extremely clean.
Food was very delicious and service was prompt and friendly. We had the lobster & tarragon and the french toast and both were super tasty.
Really good food with a inviting atmosphere.  Great service with wonderful presentation of the Food.
The food was incredibly delicious! I had the eggs Benedict with mushrooms! Wow! Will have to do that again soon.

Love the food! Amazing. Only downside was service is a bit slow. It was very busy and there weren't the appropriate number of staff working. Happened on 2 occasions. Other than that everything else is wonderful.
Service was good but the food was average. Nothing freshly made.

Naz IS the truth. He assured me that the Korean short rib would change my life and it did. Next time I will try the short rib poutine.  I have probably eaten at every breakfast place in Calgary and the is undoubtedly the best. I saw the fruit salad make a kid fall out of his chair!  Can’t wait to come back!  Stef & Bella
The food, staff and atmosphere were all incredible! Definitely going to be back again soon.
Delicious food.  Seriously interesting menu and the presentation is next level.  Great service and atmosphere too.

the food was yummy! my food came out quickly and the presentation was gorgeous. the decor of the resatuarnt is cute and i love the little unique touches like the potted plants on the tables and the milk jug water glasses and cloth napkins.

Lovely food, service, and atmosphere. Usually stick to downtown for brunch but this was worth the drive out. They have a good range of dishes and cocktails and I like being able to get on the wait list online.

Had the opportunity to dine in here before lockdown, and it was soo good! What drew me in initially was I saw they use Phil & Seb coffee which is my favourite! My only complaint is that they don’t have a location more central so I can go more often 😉

Grabbed take out and when I got home both my French toast and potato rosti were literally burnt black...won't be returning. I can understand burning something, but then to actually serve it and make me pay full price is absurd.
Love this place. One of my favorite places to go for breakfast. Great food, healthy portions. Staff were friendly and attentive.
Great atmosphere. Great staff. Great food! That's all I can say about this place.

My review of Brekkie is long over due.  Some friends and I wanted a nice hearty breakfast, and I am beyond glad that we stopped in. The first thing that is worth noting is the the warm and welcoming atmosphere. The mimosa selection is pretty neat, and definitely stands out as compared to other diners, as having more than one flavour.  I don't remember exactly what we all ordered, but the food was absolutely exquisite. This is one of the very few remaining restaurants that still makes their Hollandaise every day, with no clumping, no film on the top, I would say this is the best Hollandaise I've ever had. The fingerling potatoes are a step in the right direction for most restaurants, but the seasoning on their spuds is perfect!  I believe I had ribs or some sort of braised meat with my meal, and it was absolutely delicious.  In short, if you're looking for a breakfast diner to fall in love with, make sure you stop in to let them show you what a caring and passionate kitchen team can do, to the Chef, don't stop what you're doing, do not fall into the cost trap of making things cheaper. Your wholesome ingredients are what makes the dining experience special, and know that your efforts don't go unnoticed. Bravo Brekkie team. Until next time!
Really enjoyed the mush Benny, the salad dressing was amazing as well. Will be back

There’s always a bit of a wait when I come here, but that’s ok, you can usually get in fairly quickly. I ordered an eggs benedict and the pancakes because I can never decide. Both dishes very tasty! The pancakes were nice and fluffy, just the way I like them. Our server was very nice also.
Nice spot, should get more attention it's very good!
Great breakfasts. One of my favourite places.
Awesome breakfast menu..great eggs Benedict

Gf and I went to brunch here and the food was AMAZING!!! The truffle oil is to die for. Their lavender fog with oat milk is basically heaven. The place is so earthy and warm. I would come here everyday if I could!
Cozy place,  delicious food   good service
Best brunch we've had in a very, very long time! We had the Lobster Benedict, Korean BBQ Benedict and shared the Cardamom French Toast. Phenomenal!
It was great food and great service. My first visit won't be the last. Thank you very much for the outstanding experience! See you soon.

Yet another visit of complete incompetence. On their wait list and invited to come in for your seating only to be told that there will be another 30min wait and people are clearing skipping the queue. This seems to how things work here every time we plan on going there. They so deserve to go out of business for the worst customer service in Calgary. Drive across the toad and get a much better breakfast at Fergus and Bix!
Excellent breakfast and even better strong coffee

It took quite a while to get in. We waited over an hour to get in. However, the food was good. The kids meal was fantastic with a kids cup which is quite rare in a restaurant and they gobbled it up. Egg Benedict was nicely done as usual and the waitress were really attentive. Looking forward to our next brunch there.
Great food great service one of my hights  visiting Calary
Best pancakes i’ve tried!

Got the curry fried chicken and bubble waffle. The eggs, sauce and chicken were great. The waffle batter needs improvement, I think they use the same battery as regular waffles but it's way too dense when you put it on the bubble waffle press. The bubbles were way too dense and chewy instead of crispy and airy.
One of the best breakfast restaurants in town. Servers were rushing though which was off-putting.

I had the cardamom french toast with a side of Korean fried potatoes. Everything was so delicious and the presentation was great. I've never had french toast with such unique and interesting flavours. Our server was friendly as well. I would definitely come again!
Love Brekkie. They always have amazing food and a great staff. The only tiny complaint I have is that their portions could be a bit bigger. PS- their french toasts are to die for!!!!
So so yummy.  Stopped in from Toronto on way to LL.  Fresh, delicious, perfect portions.  Love the cornbread so much I ordered some to go.  Nice staff.  Highly recommend for a great brunch!!
Great food. Lobster bennie was fantastic
Very nice room and friendly service. The food is great and they make an incredible benedict. Their granola and fruit bowl that is accompanied by a home made frozen yogurt popsicle is amazing.
Food and Service was excellent.
Best hollandaise sauce ever! They also have giant cookies for 3 or 4 dollars. Super worth it!
Super friendly staff and excellent food that is always good!

Hands down, best breakfast spot! The hollandaise is phenomenal, as is every other item I’ve tried on the menu. Reservations are taken over the phone Mon-Fri but using the Yelp App is pretty easy on Sat and Sun.  They are also very thorough with cleaning each table between guests. Service is spectacular and it seems to be always busy. I’m happy to support this local business!
I had the mushroom benny's and it was amazing! Service was excellent. A tad pricey for breakfast.

Food is amazing at Brekkie! Reservation system was not great and they recently changed everything... so I got confused and had problems with the app. The manager was very kind and keen on solving the issue, despite the rush hour! I will certainly go back using yelp app for future reservations....

Nice eatery. They recently changed their menu which was a nice change. However, we visited the place recently (during COVID-19 pandemic) and we were surprised to see workers in the kitchen without face masks and without gloves.  Also, we were not sure social distancing was enforced as people seemed to be seated on tables that were too close.  They close at 3 pm, not too practical.
Nice service.  Food is good quality... But, only ok in execution.

Unique dishes, unlike any other in the city! Plus the interior is the cutest and really adds to the experience!  Made a reservation in advance through the yelp app to avoid a wait and the times were pretty accurate.
I will say everything average neither good nor bad, but nothing special in this location
Short rib Benny avocado toast! 😋
Tasty breakfast food in Aspen. Service was good. Recommend booking as it is a small place.

I have dined here in the past and always enjoyed the food and service. This was my first restaurant I visited since Covid-19 started and I appreciated how thorough they were with their precautions, social distancing, cleaning/sanitizing, and dividers.
Nothing to unique. Food was good.
Reasonable prices, excellent service, very good food. I won't hesitate to recommend Brekkie to my friends. We'll be back for sure!

An absolute must visit! I'm not into over-the-top dishes that only look good for a photo, but these pancakes were a delight! They were more like a light fluffy donut, and totally worth a try! They weren't over sweet, the fresh berry compote and lemon custard balanced out the sweetness of the dough. The other hot breakfasts were delicious, can't wait to visit again!

2nd review a few years later. The service was good and everything was clean. I ordered the spare rib benny with hash. It was very good the hash has different root vegetables in it that made in amazing. The benny was very good but the rib lacked flavor it was tender though.  Old review The place looks nice. The hostess took be to a table and gave me a dirty class with water I asked for a replacement but got another dirty glass. I ordered a orange juice which also came in a dirty glass. I ordered the french toast which was good but was small one slice of thick bread and a few berries.  It was a overall sad experience.

Even though we were told it was a 45 minute wait, we ended up waiting an hour and 48 minutes before being seated BUT I’m still giving this spot a full five star because their cleaning protocols were on point, service was prompt and friendly, meals came out QUICK and everything was so delicious and rich and indulgent. Would 100% return over and over and do the two hour wait. Absolutely worth it.

Amazing! Probably one of the most funky, upbeat restaurants I have ever been too. Outstanding service and the food was stunningly beautiful and tasted just as good. I had a blast and will be coming back for sure. Superb on every point.

Shout out to the team at Brekkie today! We are regulars and today we brought some friends with us who are from out of town and very picky (that's an understatement honestly!!!).  Our server Alex :) was so patient and gracious in handling their many requests and questions.... The food was  yummy - esp the avocado toast and mushroom bennie!! The cappuccinos were top notch.  And overall it was an enjoyable brunch experience! We will keep coming back!!

Had the best seller Bubble tea pancakes and I was expecting a sugar over load and instagramable content and I was pleasantly surprised to find the pancakes really delicious and fluffy the ube glaze was so good. Also interesting choice of music... I heard a lot of reggae Beatles covers this morning 😂

Wowwww; we are really impressed. My daughter and I  used to enjoy breakfast in this place but stopped eating out during Covid. After almost 5 months we are back and amazed by this team. They have done a great management to keep the place super safe, clean and sanitized. The food taste and quality Is ever better than before. Congrats Brekkie; you guys changed the threat of Covid to a better opportunity to keep your customers happy and feel like home.

OMFG. Possibly the best breakfast I have ever eaten in Calgary. Summer fruit pancakes with lemon custard were perfectly prepared, flavorful, and arrived with a gourmet presentation. Phil and Sebastian coffee was hot and brewed right in the middle of bitter and weak - tasty!  Service was friendly, attentive and prompt. I cannot wait to go back and eat my way through the rest of the menu!

Awesome service and delicious food! We ordered the braised short rib poutine and the Montreal smoked meat sandwich, both were still very tasty despite us having to drive 30 minutes before enjoying the food!
Delicious breakfast. I highly recommend this place for a quick visit

Great food because it feels fresh and different.  Much better than the restaurant that was there before. The staff are friendly and attentive. You feel welcomed.  The seating are also much better.  The menu is limited though and it's not cheap. We got seated right away as we went during the week. I am not sure if they are busy on the weekend, but they got lots of seating and enough room to wait not like before.  Location is great too with lots of parking.  Still great

Lovely spot for brunch. From the quick response to my reservation request via email, to the staff greeting you at the door, to the lovely servers, everyone was friendly and provided wonderful service that made you feel welcome and safe. Our coffee drinks came quickly and our food was beautifully plated, as usual. Would recommend getting the bubble tea pancakes if you want something fun and exciting! The atmosphere is perfect for meeting with friends and while I am sure they are busy, you never feel rushed here. Will definitely be back again soon.
Great service and pancakes!

We had a wonderful post wedding brunch here! The food was delicious and the service was even better. Great ambience and they kept the place open past regular hours just for us. Thank you for accommodating us to celebrate and enjoy our favorite meal with our close friends and family.
Loved the food, service and the cleanliness of this place.
Yum! The breakfast I got was delicious. Service was amazing. The pancakes are different from usual pancakes but delicious none the less! A bit far from where I live but worth the drive!

Horrible Burger I ordered the Spicy friend chicken burger for takeout. The outside layer was over fried to the point where I couldn't bite into it. and the inside was all chicken fat, it was also soggy.  not ordering from here again
Great atmosphere! Love all beautiful live plants! Breakfast was delicious & portions were perfect and the staff was friendly! Kelsey provided great service!

Awesome lightly fusion breakfast foods. The chicken sandwich is incredible! I will come back even though I live 30m away. My complements to the chefs for managing to control the blending of cooking cultures so well.

It's not just the craftsmanship and creativity that go into the dishes, but the quality of the ingredients is top notch, as well. We also enjoyed the attentive service, and the ambience is nice for a breakfast place. Good portion sizes that will satisfy most guests with a healthy morning appetite. Highly recommended.

Second time here. Not gonna lie, from where I live, this is a 30mim drive if not more. I love their food and sangria but it wouldn't be a place I visit often due to their location. It's great for people who loves hear here but I live in Beddington and it's a long drive. Only come here once in a while but they don't disappoint. First time here I got their Benny's and the portion isn't great. Very little meat compared to everything else. But their food are pretty exceptional

It’s Mother’s Day, 07:45. COVID. Planned on ordering take out / DoorDash from here. DoorDash says 61 minute wait. Brekkie turned off receiving orders. Called Brekkie - states too backed up and next ordering time won’t be until 2:00 PM. Did you guys not plan for increased business on the most popular breakfast day of the year?! Disappointing.
Friendly staff and good coffee
Delicious food and drinks, as well as a very cute atmosphere! Will definitely be coming back!

food is okay not worth it to wait 45mins though. Also apparently if you complain enough on how long you’ve been waiting the hostess will seat that group before everyone else on the waiting app. My gf and I saw it happen right in front of us and were shocked. The group when asked their name the hostess literally scrolled way down the list to find it yet they got seated right away.
Great food!
We really love coming in for brunch. Never feel rushed and the food is very tasty. The price is on the high end but worth it.

Had an amazing brunch here! Definitely one of Calgary's best spots. The service is amazing. Tali was our server and she was amazing. The food is so good.The Braised Short Rib Poutine and the Spicy Fried Chicken was soooo good. The special was a Bubble tea pancakes and it was so good. This place is worth the wait and hype! You can join the waitlist through the Yelp app or calling so, definitely worth it before making the trip to see what the wait is like! We definitely will be back when we're in Calgary next.

I enjoyed my lunch today as I don’t eat meat or dairy I had the mushroom eggs Benedict and asked to swap the hollandaise out for something without dairy. As per many restaurants they said they could just leave it off and I mentioned that it doesn’t seem right I should lose something because of an allergy and wanted to make sure I had a moist ingredient in exchange. I said that avocado would be great and of course it tasted fabulous. I must say I was very irritated to be charged $2.50 (without being told even)for the replacement!  I’ve been to this restaurant quite a few times and every time I would rate them 75/25. I am 75% satisfied with the ambience, food and service and 25% dissatisfied with all of the above.
Great food, always love when I get to come here for brunch.

Best breakfast spot in the city hands down. We have been to all the top spots. This one takes the cake. Absolutely gorgeous in there. Wicked staff. The food man. Unbelievable. Get the fried egg sandwich with the tom8jelly and spicy mayo. Just wow. Will definitely be back.
Monogram coffee, short rib Bennie cooked in Monogram Espresso reduction with extra Monogram Espresso juice to pour over if you want ... What's not to love!
Great food.
Food was delicious and service was quick- went on family day, it was busy but not packed. Would definitely return again!
Good food, mediocre service
I really like this restaurant! I ordered a salmon brekkie, the smoked salmon tastes super good and the whole plate is healthy. The marble table looks very classy, good choice👍

Updated Feb. 15/20.  Returned to Brekkie today for a do-over and everything was terrific!  The service was back to the standard of excellence.  Shout out to Jeremy and Percilla for their prompt follow-up.  And to our server Tyler for a job well done.  Thanks again Brekkie! (previous review)  Had breakfast here first thing Sunday morning.  The food was very good as usual.  However, this waitress just did not measure up to our previous servers.   Great food Brekkie, but as a higher-end breakfast restaurant, more training of your staff please.

Busy spot and its obvious why! Great food and atmosphere. Some really good healthy options on the menu too. They make a  mean eggs benny no doubt about that! Great hollandaise sauce. It's wonderful to see some more imaginative creations on a breakfast menu! Will be back to try the Red Velver Pancakes no doubt! If you do decide to check out this charming eatery dont miss out on their decadent drink menu! Yummy! And I recommend using the waiting list feature on the Yelp app!
Delicious breakfast with a nice amount of options. Recommend going online to get onto the wait list if you’re coming on a weekend. The coconut custard French toast was 10/10
Absolutely delicious! Portions are huge, everything is soo tasty. Get anything with the braised beef or potatoes in it. Their berry puree yogurt is also out of this world.
I like that you can check the waitlist online! Food was excellent
Excellent food, service, and atmosphere! With reasonable prices to boot!
Everything was delicious. Definitely get the Ube Purple Latte if you're unsure what to drink!

So good! Go out for breakfast regularly and it was nice to go somewhere and be like "wow, that was really good!". Quality was great, which I have felt has slid at some of my other favourite locations. Also like that they have some different options as well as twists on favourites.
Expensive
Is great. Food great. Menu great. Coffee great. Service great. Decor great.
Wonderful food, staff and atmosphere. Very busy
Always have great customer service and good meals! There never is anything I have found to not be impressed about!
Came here with a group of 3. The server was quick and it was such an easy experience. The food was delicious and it was a cute place.
Loved everything about this place! Creative menu, welcoming atmosphere and outstanding service.

Went here for brunch.  Had the short rib poutine and it was really good.  My wife had the short rib Benny and it was also really good.  The teas were really good.  Had the Lavender London Fog and was quite impressed.  We ordered a side of pancakes such had caramel apples and bacon in it and it was very good as well.  Will definitely be back for brunch again.  This place has plenty of parking.  Service was great.
Definitely new little joint for breakfast and brunch, it has a decent selection of food and the service is great. I would definitely go back if I was in the area.
Clean modern restaurant with really good food.

Nice place, good atmosphere. Portions seem a little small - but tasty. Menu is pretty standard, with some outstanding features that help elevate it. This is where the Ace Diner used to be, and if you swore that off, come in to try Brekkie because it is a whole different experience and quality.

We arrived fairly late after the morning rush and were served VERY quickly. My favourite was the pastrami sandwich with sauerkraut and mustard oh man it was great. Also the hash browns are great. Will be back

The service at Brekkies is not the best, the waiting time is ridiculous sometimes, staff don't always seem to be sure what is happening. When there is a rush at Brekkies the staff don't seem ready.  However, the food there is good and my friends and I enjoy ourselves once seated.
Has ok food but they make you wait when they have open tables available. Say they have a system for sitting people but looks like more of a lack of staffing issue.
Great food!

This breakfast place has a comfortable atmosphere. The coffee is good but the food is just average. I tried the chorizo Benedict which was okay but for $17 I expected more than 2 wafer thin pieces of chorizo that didn't even cover half the English muffin.
Food is beautifully prepared & servers very helpful in modifying for special dietary needs. Will SO be back!
Food is 3/5 but the wait to get the food as well as the price to value ratio for the portions is off. I’d expect this price on Stephen ave but not here.

Fresh off the airplane and came here for breakfast...and it was AMAZEBALLS!  The short rib poutine is to die for. (Or diet for :-) ) and can’t say enough good things about Dani our server... Top Notch!!!

Nice presentation, fast service, food was lacking flavour. Hollandaise sauce tasted like it was butter and nothing else. No seasoning .... No lemon... Was there an an egg yolk? Idk. Won't be returning. Feel like I wasted my money.

Restaurant has a nice atmosphere, but trying much too hard to be trendy and hipster. Cutlery and cups came sorta dirty. We had the fried chicken eggs Benedict and the chorizo Benedict. Food was hot and fresh when it arrived. The Hollandaise sauce was super plain and we've had better from a packet mix. Fried chicken was well cooked but under seasoned. Chorizo was tasty and added much needed flavor, but was still on the plain side. Service was nice and friendly and the wait for food was a bit long but not too bad, considering how busy the place was. Overall the food was disappointing and plain for the price, and we won't be visiting again.
Nasty
Impressively good food, healthy. Lots of parking and no wait times!
Coffee isn't good, nor is the amount of food for price.. I don't usually leave bad reviews, but there is way better value for money out there. Sorry.
Food is always tasty, friendly staff and some of the best bacon in Calgary.

My girlfriend and I went here for breakfast with a friend one morning because it's near her place and we weren't disappointed at all! Usually we'd go to OEB or something but the service here was super friendly and the food was AMAZING.  We've had a lot of french toast, it's a hard dish to get wrong but also hard to get just perfect; we thought we found "peak" french toast at the River Cafe but man Brekkie gets this one so right. The toast is thick cut and a dream; crispy outside and soft inside. The sweet cream and syrup as well as whipped cream and fruits pair so well with it, this french toast is now our new favourite. The bacon here is thick cut and the perfect amount of crispy and soft, although my girlfriend prefers more crispy she was satisfied with this.  The Brekkie Toast/Avocado toast is delicious, although in my opinion the portion is a little small for what you’re paying.  The Short Rib Poutine is hands down my favourite dish, sweet, savoury, delicious. The short rib is amazingly tender and it pairs so well with the sweet gravy and potatoes, love it.  Overall would highly recommend this place for breakfast or brunch, it was delicious!
Great food but to avoid waiting during busy weekends I recommend using the waitlist feature
Pricey but well worth it....coffee delicious too
Yummy food and friendly service! More importantly, great coffee. I will go back for sure.
On par if not better than OEB or any other breakfast place in Calgary.
One of the best brunch places we’ve been to in Calgary! The inside is also super trendy! All around a great place to eat.
Good pancakes, red velvets
Love it
(Translated by Google) Balanced food, good service and products  (Original) Comida balanceada, buena atencion y productos
Great food and wonderful atmosphere
Absolutely amazing food and service. The Coffee was on point and I can't say enough good things about the food

My plate of food was very pretty looking, however, for $17 (I got the French toast), my mood changed quite quickly when I realized that all it really was was just a slice of thick toast with a few berries, some cookie crumble, and two big mounds of whip cream on the side. It was tasty while it lasted - which was not for very long. This was very disappointing, however, my mood changed for the worse once again when I saw that I was charged $2 for a teeny tiny bit of syrup (which I was NOT told was extra and the server made it sound like she was just offering it to go with my food). My brunch buddy was also very unimpressed by her mediocre eggs Benny and hash browns, and her $3.50 miniature glass of orange juice. Total, the bill came to $43, and I wasn't even half way to being full! Since I already felt so cheated, I only tipped $5 for our awful experience, which was met with a moody and forced "thank you, sir", but that's alright because it just solidified our plan to not return. I give two stars only because I like the the decor, and the overall atmosphere of the space, and because the one time I had visited before (many months before), it was a relatively decent experience. Something must have changed since then!
Tasty brunch! Nice place, nice staff!
Cool breakfast spot!
Awesome brunch spot. Cute restaurant, delicious food.
Nice atmosphere. Good food.
Great little breakfast place. Good food. Vibrant and friendly atmosphere. I will be revisiting.
The best French Toast in town . Bar none :))) Leaves nothing to be desired except more of it!!
Best breakfast in town!

Not a trusted place.I really enjoyed going to this place , great food and interior design. But unfortunately I left my sunglasses there and when I went back  it was gone so be careful to not leave anything behind there.
Pretty good! Service is slow

Service was amazing and very fast. Eggs Benedict are some of the best I’ve ever had so I’ll definitely be coming back for more! Atmosphere and overall restaurant are definitely worth a visit. Also love the little flowers they add to dishes

Had a great breakfast at this spot. Eggs Benedict were good (although the eggs were a little over cooked, but forgivable due to high quality), great potatoes and side pancake. Coffee was also top notch.

We were a table of 11 and the service was so fast. The food was amazing everyone enjoyed their meal. I had the pancakes and they were fluffy and delicious. The other popular dish was the short ribs poutine. Check out this great place.
The best eggs Benny ! Wish I lived closer to this place or I would go every weekend
Good food, but very loud. Friendly staff.
Tasty food
Stopped in to grab a quick coffee. The owner came out and gave me a coffee because they were have temporary issues with their POS. Such a great place a chill vibes. I will be coming back!

Customer service has gone for a toss..  If you send your staff on a break they should go somewhere else..not eat behind the bar n watch people!!!! Eating not a bite, but a full plated meal  Not dining again...
100% my new favourite breakfast spot! Also their milkshakes are to die for!
The food is pretty tasty although the Benny's are lacking meat for all the dishes it's mostly bread and egg.. Over all the food was good
This place is awesome. Great service and really good food.

The poached eggs in the eggs benedict were done perfectly, without a bit of overcooked yolk. The plating is also done beautifully. I felt the maple pork was slightly too sweet, though the meat was perfectly tender. More hollandaise would have also been nice. The side potatoes were just okay, but overall lacking flavor and tasted very plain.
Been a few times now and really enjoyed the food and service. Great menu in an atmosphere filled with great service.

Great and friendly service and food. Portions were fairly bigger then average and amazing in flavour. Atmosphere is cute. A little pricier than average with most choices being between $15-24 a dish. A lot of gluten free substitutions can me made for dishes and they have good gluten free bread. But the pancakes and French toast cannot be made gluten free.
Awesome breakfast spot with really tasty dishes and good coffee. Worthy of dollar spent.
Really good. Family friendly.
Loved it here! My new favourite breakfast place. Amazing tasty food and great options for kids too. Good service, and very unique looking place. Will be back!

Brekkie is a great neighborhood breakfast spot!!  The atmosphere is warm and welcoming.  The staff is friendly and helpful with selecting dishes, customizing, and refilling your coffee.  The food is excellent and having your salt, pepper, ketchup and hot sauce at the table is a nice touch.  We will be back!
Brunch game is lit 🔥
Great food and atmosphere!
Had breakfast at this place recently, the food was really good! Alex, our server, was great - came by frequently and made sure our coffee cups were full and everything was ok!
Had breakfast with friends at Brekkie, the food was great and our server (Alex) was AMAZING.
Pricy but yummy, and lovely ambiance.

I went here for breakfast last week, first time here. I was quite disappointed with the portion size considering the price was 22 bucks for the eggs Benny I had. Don't get me wrong, the eggs Benny was good but the side was just fried potatoes with what I believe are micro greens on top. Is the microgreens what make this so expensive? I felt a bit cheated that 2 breakfasts with a coffee and tea cost just over 47 dollars( not including tip) with small portions.
Long fine brown hair in my eggs benny. Sorry I didn’t come to eat this type of protein. For this reason I was really turned off.
My first time. Great atmosphere for a lunch with family and friends.

Decor of the restaurant is very modern and the food is...AWESOME! They serve Monogram coffee for all you coffee connoisseurs out there. Definitely worth checking out....they only open till 3pm. Try and go either early in the morning or near closing to avoid lines and wait times.

Given 3 stars for creativity, food wasnt bad but $48 for 2 egg benny and 2 coffees and still hungry when leaving there are better places to go for breakfast that taste better and better value for your dollar. Side note to owners.  Leave the flower petals off the food or at least make it an option
Great food at reasonable prices.   A nice treat!
Delicious, quality food. Always very good when I visit. Reasonably priced. Wish it was open later.

Paid nearly 40$ for one person on door dash. Recieved a box of slop. Literal slop and a nearly empty coffee. No choice on eggs? And you auto send SCRAMBLED slop? Somone spending this much isnt a child. The standard if you give no selection is over easy or sunny side up. NOT SCRAMBLED SLOP. Inedible wast of my money, plus a empty "latte" that was essentially a couple drops of coffee and cold milk.  Over priced, fake, hipster garbage. If your going to charge high end prices? Do not send people scrambled slop. Toast? Does not go in a steaming box on top of your SCRAMBLED SLOP.  First time trying, local to the neighborhood and i will warn everyone away. What a waste of 40$ Would have been better off at Dennys. At least they let you pick your eggs. Not assume you are 5 years old.
Great meal. Lovely waitress. Food was well made and nicely presented
One of the most unique and tasty Bennie I have had
great place for brunch!
Was just there today. Fantastic food, highly tasty.  I mean super good! Service is fast, attentive and spot on. Check them out!

The food was amazingly delicious, the service was outstanding, and people were super friendly. There was a little bit of a wait time, but its worth it. Shout out to Jessica and Heather! They helped make it a memorable and pleasant experience! A+++

Excellent food, saw an omelette go by after I ordered, must be on a special board that wasn't shared, I'm an omlette fan, so was kind of bummed. But, as I said the food was excellent, Mimosas great, good coffee, I drink mine black, so I appreciate good coffee.  Not five 🌟 because of the missing knowledge of omlettes! Maybe next time, now that I have inside knowledge!

Great option for brunch on the weekend. Used the no wait app/Yelp app. We tried their Grilled Chorizo and Ghost Pepper Coulis Benny, Wild mushroom Benny and AvocadoToast. My girlfriend and I both enjoyed our bennies. The chorizo had the right amount of heat. Will most likely make this one of our go to places for brunch.
I only deduct a star because I had my heart set on huevos rancheros, which happens not to be on the menu. But this is a really good place. Thanks, all, for a lovely start to my day!
The service, atmosphere, and food was amazing! Everything was unique and super tasty; with great portions. I got one of the bowls and needed help to finish it, but it was so good.
Very good breakfast cafe, great service!
As always the service and food were both excellent
Outstanding in every aspect!!!
Such great quality food, very friendly staff and super prompt service every time we’ve gone. A great place for anyone looking for celiac-friendly food. Highly recommend
Great service and food
Really great atmosphere, a great place to relax and grab a bite in the West Springs area
Super tasty food and a great environment. Definitely will go back.
Super fresh and delicious, good atmosphere, perfect brunch spot! We shared the mushroom short rib bowl and fried egg sandwich both were amazing.
Nice cozy brunch place in Wentworth!
Can be very busy on the weekends but we enjoyed our meal.. I will recommend
The food was really good! I had the chicken and waffles. The prices were a bit higher than other high end brunch places but it was definitely worth it.
Food is innovatively prepared and very tasty and fresh. Service was quite good as well.

So glad I found this place! They have a great menu (even have health conscious options).The service is outstanding and the food comes out pretty quick so no waiting forever when you’re starving:) the staff are friendly and check in with you regularly to make sure everything is okay.  What an awesome local business! Give it a try!
Great breakfast place. A little out of the way, but the food is high quality.
Delicious food, great atmosphere, excellent service
Good food, great service. Overall good experience and worth a visit if you're in the area.

The place is super cute and well decorated. It took us long time to get us our water and menus and after we told the waitress, she was super attentive and gave us our meal for half off. Great service and delicious food!

I have to admit, Brekkie has thoroughly impressed me. I've been here twice now, and I can see that they are a business WANTING to make improvements, which can't be said of all businesses. They learn from their experiences. To note, I visited Brekkie on the labor day long weekend and they struggled a bit with seating everyone. However, on my next visit, they had this all fixed. In fact, they were leveraging the NoWait app even better and trying to seat everyone in order (not actively giving priority to the app or those waiting) which is nice to see. Their food is also great. Recommend the bennie's. The ghost pepper sauce is HOT! Be careful, and they do warn you about that. Service was great, quick and personal. Overall, I would say visit Brekkie! Their cool, quaint location is really a great foundation for their business and I'm so glad to see that they are always actively trying to improve! Don't be afraid to give them feedback, they are truly receptive. Good luck to Brekkie! I'll see you again in the future for brunch!

Excellent breakfast stop, chorizo benny with ghost pepper sauce has just the right amount of heat for a fall morning. Egg yolks runny and whites poaxhed nice and firm, I am sure the rest of the food is just as good, it was starting to get busy at 7:45 in the am...

Place was busy which is usually a great sign. The service was great friendly and personable. The food was delicious I had the eggs benedict  and a side sausage. I think my only feedback would be bigger bottles of pelligrino 750ml instead of 250ml. The decor was nice great service and food winning formula much better then the ace breakfast place that was in the spot prior.

Went to this lovely place because snow made us take a detour on our banff trip. I had the Moroccan chicken egg benedict and the gf had the chicken and waffle. For the price, the portion is relatively small. BUT, they both taste amazing. The Moroccan chicken is a curry chicken and it compliments the holindaise sauce nicely. The potato feels out of place though. It felt like they didn't put any effort in making the potatoes special. The chicken and waffle is not your regular fried chicken. The chicken has a complex taste. The waffle is fluffy. I would say it's a pancake and waffle hybrid. The service was excellent. Our server was friendly and attentive. We will be back for more.
Amazing food.
I have many allergies and they always accommodate me. No fuss and excellent food every time.

Ok. Overpriced for what you get. Food was good, but not excellent. Service was great. Food looked amazing but tasted average. My homemade pancakes or French toast were just as good. Flower petals did not justify the $9 per 2 strips of chocolate covered bacon. 2 small pieces of bacon. Likely will not come back for the average meal for 2 adults 2 kids for $80

We just loved our experience here  on a Saturday morning  in every way.    I experience started by calling to check on the wait time. Although we were not there, they put us on the list and by the time we arrived we were ready to be seated.  This was very much appreciated.  The decour, ambience and trendy atmosphere  including the presentation of each dish  complete with fresh flower petals blew us away. Service was excellent!
Great food!!
You won't find a better breakfast joint in the city. Staff is courteous, and the food they serve ranges from awesome and healthy to down right heart cloggingly delicious.

Whether it was an excellent job hiring or great training, the staff did an epic job. We had a very busy table with 4 little ones with us and our server was on the ball, very friendly and patient with us. The food was next level, and different from anywhere else in town. Highly recommended breakfast joint.
Paid 20 dollars for 2 little pieces of chicken and a waffle, it tasted good but it really wasn’t 20 Dollars worth of food.
Food was flavourful and fresh. Attention to detail on presentation. Staff were friendly and the atmosphere is casual and inviting. Definitely going back 🍳🥗🥑!

Drove from Airdrie to this cute little breakfast spot I found through CuriosityCalgary. Drive wasn’t great due to the construction happening in the area but the place was easy to find within the complex, with adequate parking. The decor was super cute, server/host was nice, food was bland. I ordered a traditional benny while by bf ordered a pork belly benny. The egg was waaay over cooked, with a hard orange yolk. The hollandaise resembled the remnants of a flavourless foamy egg. The pork belly was hard and dry. They topped their benny’s with microherbs and edible flowers, when they should have been using salt and pepper.

Great brunch spot, nice bright location and a good menu. French toast sticks and pancake skewers were definitely put on the menu by someone who knows kids. I had the pork belly breakfast sandwich and really appreciated the thick cut belly cooked right.  Oh, and that Monogram coffee is awesome. Will come back
Heavenly! Amazing food and very bubbly staff! Highly recommend for brunch!
Amazing food, highly recommend using the nowait app to get a table. Great service and delicious food!

Just had breakfast here for the first time and as it is very close to our house we were excited to try it. The menu is very different from most breakfast  places and that can play both ways. In our case it did not meet with our taste (to be  clear the food was obviously prepared well and the presentation was very good)  We went Sunday morning when you expect to pay more and get something different (special) for breakfast.  I had the crab and asparagus benny because I really like the taste of crab, between the taste of the hash browns used instead of the traditional muffin to serve the Benny and the hollandaise sauce I would be hard pressed to  say it was crab.  The hash brown as a base is a good idea but it can't overpower the main ingredients, and the hollandaise  suffered the same problem (for my taste). The service was OK but considering there were only five tables seated at that time it should have been better. Probably more of a problem was that at no time were we asked how was our food or our experience, a new venture it would seem would want feedback. Add to this a bill for $53.00 for a Benny and a order of French toast with two cups of coffee plus tip, and I  have a hard time recommending this a place I  would go to on a regular basis. I will give it a while and may give them another chance but at this time improvement is needed.  Ian McLaren
This was the best breakfast! The presentation was fabulous. High compliments to the chef and staff.

Food was very good and fresh. Service was friendly and attentive.  Can't wait to go back! I had the chorizo Benny and it was awesome. The ghost Pepper sauce was not as hot as I was expecting but it was still great.

I would have rated a 4 but I feel that they normally would execute better - I just came at a bad time.  Was thrilled to find these guys had filled the breakfast gap in my neighbourhood. Only 7 weeks old, I walked in not really sure what to expect. What I discovered was truly unique. If you cross-bred a vegan with a carnivore you’d get Brekkie. The menu boasts healthy bowls and kombucha tea to breakfast dishes with sides of meaty goodness. I have the three eggs which came with fried pork belly, brisket and thick cut bacon. A halved tomato topped with a nice pesto sauce and herbed potatoes. My friend had the eggs sandwich with pork belly and pineapple salsa. The only downs I found was initial contact with staff to place an order was a little long but so friendly once they got past the rush that had just hit. The other were the potatoes which felt like they had been sitting in oil, they were so greasy I couldn’t eat them. The rest of the dish was magic - meat sweats for days! For breakfast it’s on the higher end of the price scale but you really get something different than everywhere else. Not the place for a classic brekkie that’s for sure! The vibe and decor was fresh and open with high ceilings and bright colours. Will return for sure!

This diner has a lot to offer both in scenery and palate. It was amazing food plus there is a cute waiter so you have some eye candy while you eat the tasty food;) I had the goat cheese, berries and almond toast with a side of bacon! My friend had the Chroizo Bennies! Both meals were tasty!

Service was super fast! At first I received the wrong order but the staff and kitchen corrected that quickly.  I little on the pricey side, but they offer some unique breakfast options with not so ordinary ingredients.  Seems to be an improvement from the old Ace Diner that was in this location.
Food is fantastic and service was fast. Great addition to our neighbourhood!
Overpriced and really bland with small portions.. really wanted to like it.
